{
  "text": "(iv) In woody species, most of the N tends to be organically bound. In herbaceous species in nutrient-rich soils, part of the N can be present in the form of nitrate. However, most of this would be in the petiole, which is not included in LNC measurement. et al. (1997a) ; [CITATION_1] ; [CITATION_2] ; .",
